The restocks, random releases and scheduled releases are all accurately posted and timing is almost immediate for restocks - man has to have his phone glued to his hand because nothing is ever missed and time-wise the links/details are posted well in advance of some of the bigger/mainstream apps.   Pay for the app, it's worth it, I've been successful in copping, most if not all, restocks I wanted and that is largely due to this app. The J23 team is responsive and interacts with their followers/app users.  I can't say enough good things about the app - if I were to provide a suggestion for an enhancement, it would be for notifications to be fully integrated with the native notifications (for me, Android). I actually use text notifications via twitter (when @J23app tweets) so I receive notification that way which has no issues but would just like to see it fully integrated.
